- Thus, Interest Receivable Initial Value = 0.00

Step 2: Calculate the ending Interest Receivable balance at the last date given (2024-01-29).

- For each entry, we take the amount and sum all to get the total interest receivable amount outstanding at the end.

- Next 8 entries = 8*323.48 = 2587.84

Sum till 2024-01-14 = 2407.29 + 2587.84 = 4995.13

- 2024-01-15: 312.16 -> 4995.13 + 312.16 = 5307.29  
- 2024-01-16: 295.13 -> 5307.29 + 295.13 = 5602.42  
- Next 13 days (2024-01-17 to 2024-01-29 except two last days) with amount 259.53 each:

We have:

Dates: 2024-01-17 to 2024-01-27 = 11 days x 259.53 = 2854.83  
Sum = 5602.42 + 2854.83 = 8457.25  

- 2024-01-28: 255.08 -> 8457.25 + 255.08 = 8712.33  
- 2024-01-29: 255.08 -> 8712.33 + 255.08 = 8967.41  

So total Interest Receivable End Value = 8967.41 approximately.
